    "body": "Such a fixed table becomes ineffective as soon as you have structs or mappings. I would prefer the compiler to do things like output size information about the types used. On the other hand, if a blockchain explorer wanted to make any use of the value in storage, it has to know its encoding anyway and the encoding (and the order of the variables) is everything you need to compute the location.\n",
